b'\n    Faculty  '
b'Peter Pfanner'
b'\xc2\xa0'
b'Peter Pfanner\xc2\xa0\nExecutive Director, UIC Innovation Center\xc2\xa0\nResearch Professor, Industrial Design\xc2\xa0\nResearch Professor, Department of Urology\xc2\xa0pfanner@uic.eduinnovationcenter.uic.edu'
b'pfanner@uic.edu'
b'innovationcenter.uic.edu'
b'MA, Design Methods, Illinois Institute of Technology\xc2\xa0\nBS, Applied Science in Environmental Design, University of Canberra Australia'
b'Peter Pfanner is an industrial designer, interaction designer, experience designer, innovator and educator. Currently, Peter serves as the Executive Director of the UIC Innovation Center, a collaborative, education and development center that operates at the nexus of research, education and industry. Through targeted programs and initiatives, the Innovation Center brings together students and faculty across a wide spectrum of backgrounds and experience to work on internal and external projects, driving multidisciplinary innovation and inspiring new innovators.\xc2\xa0'
b'Over the past three decades, Peter has served as design and creative director of numerous projects around the world. His experience spans mobile communications, consumer electronics, medical, office products, furniture, architecture and materials science at consultancies, corporations and universities.\xc2\xa0\n\xc2\xa0\nPeter\xe2\x80\x99s work has been featured in the Art Institute of Chicago \xe2\x80\x9cMusecast,\xe2\x80\x9d, the Art Institute of Chicago A+D series \xe2\x80\x9cYoung Chicago,\xe2\x80\x9d Business Week, Forbes.com, Brand Week, the Cooper Hewitt National Design Museum \xe2\x80\x9cDesign Culture Now,\xe2\x80\x9d and I.D. Magazine, among others.\xc2\xa0'
b'The recipient of IDSA/IDEA/Business Week, IF Design Hanover , Red Dot, Cooper Hewitt Museum, New York, Good Design, Chicago, I.D. Magazine and GE Plastics Design awards, he has exhibited work at The Art Institute of Chicago, MOMA New York, Cooper Hewitt Museum New York, Chicago Athenaeum, and I.D. Magazine Annual Design Review New York.'
b'Peter holds 17 design and utility patents and is a 1st Dan Black Belt in Tae Kwon-do.'
